A shop submits a quote in one of two modes:                                                                                          
                                                                                                                                       
  ┌──────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┐                            
  │                  │       Mode A: Simple Total Price       │      Mode B: Line Items (Positions)       │
  ├──────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Fields used      │ priceMinMinorUnits, priceMaxMinorUnits │ lineItems[] list                          │
  ├──────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ Total calculated │ Directly from the fields               │ Auto-summed from all line items           │                            
  ├──────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ When             │ No lineItems provided                  │ lineItems provided (ignores priceMin/Max) │
  └──────────────────┴────────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────────────────────────────┘

  ---
  Mode A: Simple Total Price

  - priceMinMinorUnits — required, >= 0 (in grosz/cents)
  - priceMaxMinorUnits — optional, >= 0, must be >= min. If omitted, defaults to min (= fixed price)
  - So: single price = only provide min (max auto-equals min). Range = provide both.
  - currency — required, max 3 chars (e.g. "PLN")
  - estimatedDays — optional, must be >= 1 if provided
  - note — optional, max 2000 chars

  ---
  Mode B: Line Items (Positions)

  Each line item has two sub-modes (XOR — pick exactly one per item):

  Sub-mode 1: Total price per position

  - totalPriceMinMinor — required, >= 0
  - totalPriceMaxMinor — optional, defaults to min. Must be >= min.
  - workPrice* and partsPrice* must be null

  Sub-mode 2: Work + Parts breakdown

  - workPriceMinMinor / workPriceMaxMinor — optional pair (labor cost)
  - partsPriceMinMinor / partsPriceMaxMinor — optional pair (materials)
  - At least one of work or parts must be provided
  - Each max defaults to its min if omitted
  - totalPrice* must be null

  Per line item fields:

  - position — int >= 0 (ordering)
  - description — required, non-blank, max 500 chars

  Can line items be mixed? YES

  Each line item independently chooses its sub-mode. So in a single quote:
  - Position 0: total price 500 PLN (fixed)
  - Position 1: work 200–300, parts 150 (range + fixed)
  - Position 2: total price 100–200 (range)

  This is perfectly valid. The constraint is per line item — you can't mix total + work/parts within the same item.

  ---
  Quote-level total (Mode B)

  The quote's priceMinMinorUnits and priceMaxMinorUnits are auto-calculated:
  - min = SUM of each item's getMinTotal() (totalMin, or workMin + partsMin)
  - max = SUM of each item's getMaxTotal() (totalMax, or workMax + partsMax)